In recent years, the Chinese government has issued a series of regulations and measures to improve coal mine safety. Coal is the major energy resource in China, covering 67 percent of the country's consumption structure of all primary energy resources. Official statistics said that from January to September this year, 4,228 people were killed in 2,337 coal mine accidents. Up to Oct. 10, there were 43 major accidents nationwide. A major accident means more than 10 deaths at one time. 